In the UPLC-QTOF-MS dataset, a total of 4596 features were detected in the positive mode (2537) and negative mode (2059) after pooled QC filtering of CV < 30%. Further, after annotation using the Human Metabolome Database (HMDB) (https://hmdb.ca/spectra/ ms/search), we obtained that 1532 metabolite features in both positive mode and negative mode were used for statistical analysis. The overall composition of the distributions of these metabolites via principal component analysis found complex underlying correlations;
Metabolites 2023, 13, 899 7 of 23
in particular, the first principal component explained 17.7% of the total variation in the levels of these 1532 metabolites (Supplementary Figures S1 and S2A,B).
